<text layer="theta" matrix="1 0 0 1 -0.172964 -6.27725" transformations="translations" pos="16 112" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="368" height="14.774" depth="9.8" valign="top" size="large">Wenn $x_1$ und $\bar{x}_i$ beide \texttt{False} sind, dann muss der untere Knoten vom Dreieck auch \texttt{False} gefärbt sein.</text>
<text layer="eta" matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 119.676 -193.172" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="red" type="label" width="23.536" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{False}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 145.972 -167.476" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="blue" type="label" width="18.829" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{True}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 87.6955 -159.13" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="darkgreen" type="label" width="32.951" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{Neutral}</text>
<text layer="iota" matrix="1 0 0 1 0.10498 -38.8444" transformations="translations" pos="16 112" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="368" height="13.61" depth="8.64" valign="top" size="large">Wenn aber eines von $x_1$ und $\bar{x}_i$  \texttt{True} gefäbrt ist, dann können wir den unteren Knoten vom Dreieck \texttt{True} färben.</text>
<text matrix="0.727298 -0.686321 0.686321 0.727298 -89.9546 55.471" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="blue" type="label" width="18.829" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{True}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 119.676 -193.172" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="blue" type="label" width="18.829" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{True}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 145.972 -167.476" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="red" type="label" width="23.536" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{False}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 87.6955 -159.13" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="darkgreen" type="label" width="32.951" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{Neutral}</text>
<text layer="kappa" matrix="1 0 0 1 -0.21895 -66.4933" transformations="translations" pos="16 112" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="368" height="7.807" depth="2.82" valign="top" size="large">Wir haben also ein OR-Gadget gebaut. Nun verknüpfen wir das mit $x_n$.</text>
<text layer="lambda" matrix="1 0 0 1 -4.16966 -45.7738" transformations="translations" pos="16 160" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="368" height="8.252" depth="3.26" valign="top" size="large">$C = x_1 \vee \bar{x}_j \vee x_n$</text>
<use matrix="1 0 0 1 85.0307 -36.8089" name="mark/disk(sx)" pos="80 192" size="large" stroke="black"/>
<use matrix="1 0 0 1 85.0307 -36.8089" name="mark/disk(sx)" pos="128 192" size="large" stroke="black"/>
