<text layer="lambda" matrix="1 0 0 1 9.42716 -20.4675" transformations="translations" pos="181.465 184.228" stroke="black" type="label" width="7.833" height="6.808" depth="0" valign="baseline" style="math">C</text>
<text layer="nu" matrix="1 0 0 1 0.40279 -35.4608" transformations="translations" pos="128 128" stroke="black" type="minipage" width="256" height="6.865" depth="1.88" valign="top">Hiermit sagen wir: $C$ muss \texttt{True} sein.</text>
<text layer="xi" matrix="0.862761 0.505612 -0.505612 0.862761 286.233 -166.272" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="blue" type="label" width="18.829" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{True}</text>
<text layer="upsilon" transformations="translations" pos="16.8193 62.5871" stroke="black" type="label" width="125.683" height="6.926" depth="1.93" valign="baseline">Case 1: $x_1, \bar{x}_i , x_n$ alle \texttt{False}.</text>
<text layer="omicron" matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 222.14 -116.746" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="red" type="label" width="23.536" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{False}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 23.6551 -115.061" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="red" type="label" width="23.536" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{False}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 328.382 -121.61" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="red" type="label" width="23.536" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{False}</text>
<text layer="pi" matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 216.594 -215.122" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="darkgreen" type="label" width="32.951" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{Neutral}</text>
<text layer="rho" matrix="0.999566 -0.029452 0.029452 0.999566 55.4202 -199.254" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="red" type="label" width="23.536" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{False}</text>
<text layer="sigma" matrix="1 0 0 1 10.5041 -9.52785" transformations="translations" pos="14.0767 164.916" stroke="red" type="label" width="87.311" height="6.926" depth="1.93" valign="baseline">von \texttt{False} umgeben</text>
<text layer="tau" matrix="1 0 0 1 0.766109 -17.2171" transformations="translations" pos="16.8193 62.5871" stroke="black" type="label" width="94.846" height="6.812" depth="1.49" valign="baseline">Case 2.1: $x_1$ ist \texttt{True}.</text>
<text layer="sigma" matrix="1 0 0 1 11.9487 -24.4385" transformations="translations" pos="14.0767 164.916" stroke="red" type="label" width="82.275" height="6.918" depth="0" valign="baseline">nicht mehr färbbar</text>
<text layer="omega" matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 23.6551 -115.061" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="blue" type="label" width="18.829" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{True}</text>
<text layer="phi" matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 99.1009 -193.906" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="blue" type="label" width="18.829" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{True}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 166.829 -214.62" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="red" type="label" width="23.536" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{False}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 62.1607 -177.196" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="red" type="label" width="23.536" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{False}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 144.808 -167.892" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="darkgreen" type="label" width="32.951" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{Neutral}</text>
<text matrix="0.964912 0.262573 -0.262573 0.964912 213.281 -214.358" pos="85.1974 346.63" stroke="darkgreen" type="label" width="32.951" height="5.479" depth="0" valign="baseline" size="small">\texttt{Neutral}</text>
<text matrix="1 0 0 1 -6.08924 -0.987149" transformations="translations" pos="122.201 46.4009" stroke="darkgreen" type="label" width="140.69" height="6.926" depth="1.93" valign="baseline">Gültig, egal was $\bar{x}_i$ und $x_n$ sind.</text>
<text layer="chi" matrix="1 0 0 1 0.280174 -31.3983" transformations="translations" pos="16.8193 62.5871" stroke="black" type="label" width="156.306" height="6.926" depth="1.93" valign="baseline">Case 2.2: $\bar{x}_i$ ist \texttt{True}. Geht Analog.</text>
<text layer="psi" matrix="1 0 0 1 -0.606277 -44.1612" transformations="translations" pos="16.8193 62.5871" stroke="black" type="label" width="100.227" height="6.812" depth="1.49" valign="baseline">Case 2.3: $x_n$ ist \texttt{True}. </text>
